717826f-a.title: Manhattan: Broadway - 216th Street
717826f-a.text:
Broadway, east side, from 216th to 218th Streets (there is no
217th Street), showing the intersection of Broadway with Tenth
Avenue. The large building in the centre is the carbarn of the
Third Avenue Railway Company.
October 26, 1927.
P. L. Sperr.
SL ~42

717827f-a.title: Manhattan: Broadway - 216th Street
717827f-a.text:
5063-5085 Broadway, west side, opposite 216th Street.
October 26, 1927.
P. L. Sperr.

717828f-a.title: Manhattan: Broadway - 216th Street
717828f-a.text:
A vacant lot at 5069-5071 Broadway, Opposite 216th Street, show-
ing in the background a brick mansion on Park Terrace East.
June 8, 1933.
P. L. Sperr.
